      "amount": "2 tablespoons"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "In a large bowl, combine tripe, lemon juice, garlic, ginger, cumin, coriander, paprika, salt, and black pepper. Mix well and set aside to marinate for at least 2 hours.",
    "Preheat a grill or grill pan to medium-high heat.",
    "Thread the marinated tripe onto skewers, leaving a little space between each piece.",
    "Brush the skewers with olive oil and grill for 4-5 minutes per side, or until the tripe is cooked through and slightly charred.",
    "Transfer the skewers to a plate and top each piece with butter.",
    "Serve immediately, garnished with chopped fresh parsley or cilantro if desired."
  ],
